<HEAD>Man Stabbed To Death At RFK Stadium Dance Concert</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 20-year-old Virginia man was stabbed to
death and two teen-agers suffered knife wounds when violence
erupted at a dance concert at Robert F. Kennedy Stadium, police
said Sunday.
   Sean Shorts, 20, of suburban Alexandria, died from stab wounds
at 8 p.m. Saturday at the Washington Hospital Center, District of
Columbia detective Norman Brooks said.
   One teen-ager was admitted to another hospital with a stab wound
to the chest. He was listed in good condition Sunday. Another youth
was released after treatment for a superficial cut.
   Police estimated 4,000 people attended the Out of School Boogie
Concert given by a group called Rare Essence, which plays go-go, a
form of dance music popular with teen-agers in the nation's capital.
   Fighting erupted at about 7:45 p.m., just 15 minutes before the
concert was scheduled to end. The concert, which included eight
bands, began early in the afternoon.
   Police said they were not sure if the stabbings were related.
