<HEAD>Parisian Wins Waiters' Race, Followed by a Japanese</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Frenchman Marc Fabre, primed in the frenzy of a
Parisian cafe, won the annual waiter's race on Sunday, crossing the
finish line with a bottle and three glasses still upright on his
tray after a five-mile hike around town.
   A Japanese waiter, Sakai Osamu, placed second, scurrying to the
finish ahead of about 500 other participants.
   The race, which started and ended at City Hall, took the servers
on a jaunt by some of Paris' landmarks, including Notre Dame and
the Paris Opera.
   The competitors were not timed.
