<HEAD>30 Injured When Grandstand Collapses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VERSAILLES, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A grandstand collapsed Sunday during
festivities to celebrate links between a French and West German
town, and 30 people were slightly injured, officials said.
   Seventeen people attending the festivities at the La Tour
d'Hautil chateau west of Paris were rushed to hospitals in
surrounding suburbs for examinations, but most suffered simply
bruises and scrapes, fire officials said.
   They said seven children were among the injured when the stands,
which rose eight feet, collapsed.
   The festivities marked the 20th anniversary since the French
town of Triel and the West German town of Selingenstadt became
sister cities.
   German firefighters taking part in the celebration helped in the
rescue operation.
   Only one of several stands on the grounds collapsed.
   Officials in nearby Versailles said the festivities continued.
   Officials were investigating the collapse.
