<HEAD>Stabbed Crewman Airlifted From Luxury Liner</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PLYMOUTH, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A crewman stabbed on the Queen
Elizabeth 2 luxury cruise ship was airlifted from the vessel Sunday
and police detectives boarded the QE 2 to investigate, authorities
said.
   The Filipino crewman, who was in his 30s, was taken by a Royal
Air Force helicopter to a Plymouth hospital where he was in stable
condition, police Constable Adrian Gale said in an interview. He
did not identify the victim.
   A Royal Air Force spokesman, who was not identified in keeping
with regulations, said he did not know how the stabbing occurred.
   Five detectives boarded the ship and would remain aboard as it
sailed from Plymouth to Southampton, southwest of London, Gale said.
   He said he did not know where the QE2 had sailed from before
entering Plymouth Sound and the offices of Cunard, the vessel's
owner, were closed.
   Gale said the 67,000-ton ship paused in Plymouth Sound outside
the port while the crewman was taken off.
</TEXT>
